_Pa’al_ Active Participle for shorushim with a middle ו:
The [[_pa’al_ active participle]] has a special conjugation for shorushim with a middle ו (also known as “two letter shorushim”) like רוץ (running):
|            | *Masculine* | *Feminine* |
| *Singular* | רָץ <br> _rautz_ <br> [he is] running | רָצָה <br> _rautzau_ <br> [she is] running |
| *Plural*   | רָצִים <br> _rautzim_ <br> [those men are] running | רָצוֹת <br> _rautzos_ <br> [those women are] running |
You can take any shoresh with a weak middle litter and replace the letters ר and צ in the conjugations above with the first and last letters of your shoresh to produce the _pa’al_ active participle of the given shoresh, (unless the shoresh has additional irregular features.)
